497
00:29:39.252 --> 00:29:41.072
animals, as you can see here,

498
00:29:42.192 --> 00:29:46.012
and that the tumors that form were infiltrated

499
00:29:46.022 --> 00:29:49.932
by T cells and other cells, and that

500
00:29:50.172 --> 00:29:54.012
by blocking T cells specifically, and in this case CD8 T cells,

501
00:29:54.432 --> 00:29:55.752
the phenotype could be reverted.

502
00:29:57.132 --> 00:30:01.092
So we thought we had a model that we could study, and because the cells, as

503
00:30:01.152 --> 00:30:04.732
I mentioned, are largely immunogenic, we have to grow them

504
00:30:05.172 --> 00:30:08.712
first in immunodeficient animal, transplant them into an

505
00:30:08.752 --> 00:30:12.692
immunocompetent animal, and then if we want to study immunotherapy, we can do

506
00:30:12.732 --> 00:30:16.232
that efficiently at this point because these tumors become very, very

507
00:30:16.252 --> 00:30:17.892
responsive to immune checkpoint blockade.

508
00:30:19.072 --> 00:30:22.502
To a point that I've never seen before, and that was really promising and

509
00:30:23.612 --> 00:30:24.372
exciting for us.

