So when we treated with temozolomide and cisplatin alone with IgG or vehicle

1210
01:10:43.166 --> 01:10:43.566
control,

1211
01:10:44.466 --> 01:10:46.326
we didn't get that much of an improvement with that.

1212
01:10:46.486 --> 01:10:50.046
But when we added anti-PD-1 to that, we did get a cure rate in some of these mice

1213
01:10:50.206 --> 01:10:52.246
in an intraperitoneal model of an MSS tumor.

1214
01:10:54.496 --> 01:10:58.466
And then in terms of toxicity, on the left there I have the

1215
01:10:58.506 --> 01:11:02.316
TMB gain with the combination of temozolomide and

1216
01:11:02.346 --> 01:11:05.126
cisplatin in cell lines, and you get an increase of

1217
01:11:05.506 --> 01:11:09.486
125 mutations per megabase gain. In

1218
01:11:09.526 --> 01:11:11.536
normal tissues, in this case in healthy tissues,

1219
01:11:12.726 --> 01:11:14.546
and this is bone marrow and lung,

1220
01:11:15.406 --> 01:11:18.526
we saw a very small increase in mutations per megabase.

1221
01:11:18.546 --> 01:11:21.986
You can see there are less than one mutations per megabase increased.

1222
01:11:22.426 --> 01:11:25.386
So a big difference in what's happening in the tumor than what's happening in

1223
01:11:25.426 --> 01:11:28.526
normal tissue. Why that difference exists, I don't know.

1224
01:11:28.546 --> 01:11:29.655
But there's probably other

1225
01:11:32.486 --> 01:11:36.226
DNA repair mechanisms in normal tissue and a lower

1226
01:11:36.306 --> 01:11:38.166
division rate that are responsible for that.

1227
01:11:38.226 --> 01:11:41.486
Although bone marrow has a higher division rate that approximates many tumors.

1228
01:11:43.066 --> 01:11:46.886
And when we looked histologically at where we were seeing loss

1229
01:11:46.946 --> 01:11:50.886
of mismatch repair, it was on the cancer cells, and the healthy tissues were

1230
01:11:50.946 --> 01:11:52.166
spared in the microenvironment.

1231
01:11:55.706 --> 01:11:55.846
So

1232
01:11:56.766 --> 01:11:59.346
given that these drugs were used in patients,

1233
01:12:00.266 --> 01:12:02.066
we decided to go forward with a clinical trial.

1234
01:12:02.446 --> 01:12:05.886
And we did a clinical trial that combined temozolomide,

1235
01:12:05.926 --> 01:12:08.426
cisplatin, and PD-1 blockade with nivolumab.

1236
01:12:09.766 --> 01:12:13.586
We wanted to ideally first treat with temozolomide and cisplatin, and then later

1237
01:12:13.626 --> 01:12:17.606
after we confirmed a higher TMB treat with anti-PD-1, but we wouldn't

1238
01:12:17.626 --> 01:12:20.886
have gotten any patients to enroll, and the IRBs were resistant to that.

1239
01:12:21.366 --> 01:12:24.946
But what we did see was a general increase in TMB in these patients

1240
01:12:25.546 --> 01:12:27.686
and a general increase in the MSI score.

1241
01:12:28.226 --> 01:12:31.406
We didn't reach our primary endpoint, which was primarily due to response,

1242
01:12:32.286 --> 01:12:33.706
but we did see an induction

1243
01:12:34.986 --> 01:12:38.856
pharmacodynamically of a mismatch repair deficiency signature in patients after

1244
01:12:38.946 --> 01:12:39.306
treatment.

1245
01:12:40.266 --> 01:12:43.986
And what we did was then looked at subgroups of these

1246
01:12:44.006 --> 01:12:47.306
patients that we treated. And these were the patients that were treated, are

1247
01:12:47.346 --> 01:12:49.706
patients with colorectal cancer that was treatment refractory.

1248
01:12:50.406 --> 01:12:53.986
And the patients that did the best and that had the longest survival were those

1249
01:12:54.026 --> 01:12:57.866
that not only had a high TMB gain but also had a

1250
01:12:57.926 --> 01:13:01.446
gain in mismatch repair deficiency score as measured by circulating tumor DNA.

1251
01:13:02.266 --> 01:13:05.966
So while this didn't hit a home run like we

1252
01:13:06.006 --> 01:13:08.426
saw in the mice, we've got some

1253
01:13:09.526 --> 01:13:13.346
important information here. So where are we going next?

1254
01:13:13.466 --> 01:13:17.106
Well, we're going to try to find new inhibitors similar to the ones that

1255
01:13:17.116 --> 01:13:20.726
Knyoh4 is using to marry with cisplatin or platinum agents.

1256
01:13:20.786 --> 01:13:24.746
We think that you have to lower mismatch repair deficiency and then add

1257
01:13:24.766 --> 01:13:27.126
a platinum agent to accelerate the whole process.

1258
01:13:27.726 --> 01:13:31.206
And we found a number through an in silico screening methodology where we treated

1259
01:13:31.246 --> 01:13:35.195
with 72 hoursWith a variety of different drugs, and we can find drugs

1260
01:13:35.226 --> 01:13:37.406
that decrease the expression of MSH2.

1261
01:13:38.146 --> 01:13:41.366
We also have a GFP reporter that has a

1262
01:13:42.286 --> 01:13:46.206
frameshift mutation that is out of sync or out of line

1263
01:13:46.226 --> 01:13:50.116
with the GFP expression. If it induces an insertion or

1264
01:13:50.166 --> 01:13:53.066
deletion there that reconstitutes GFP, we can see expression.

1265
01:13:53.776 --> 01:13:57.746
And we've already found that a few drugs that recapitulate the loss of mismatch

1266
01:13:57.756 --> 01:13:58.486
repair deficiency.

1267
01:13:59.426 --> 01:14:02.646
There's also other maneuvers that we can do clinically that I think will be

1268
01:14:02.686 --> 01:14:06.326
effective going forward. So I don't think that the failure of the initial clinical

1269
01:14:06.386 --> 01:14:10.366
trial is a message that this approach

1270
01:14:10.426 --> 01:14:13.446
won't work. I think actually it's a first step showing that it might work.

1271
01:14:14.886 --> 01:14:15.626
So in conclusion,

1272
01:14:16.706 --> 01:14:20.306
temozolomide and cisplatin induce MMRD genotype

1273
01:14:21.126 --> 01:14:22.786
and a phenotype that's immunogenic.

1274
01:14:22.866 --> 01:14:26.726
So pharmacologically, we can recreate what we see in patients with

1275
01:14:26.746 --> 01:14:29.066
mismatch repair deficiency in the native form,

1276
01:14:29.966 --> 01:14:31.806
and it increases sensitivity to PD-1 blockade.

1277
01:14:32.466 --> 01:14:34.546
Healthy tissues appear to be spared.

1278
01:14:34.656 --> 01:14:38.526
And in the example that Alberto gave on CMMRD, which

1279
01:14:38.546 --> 01:14:42.126
are children who are born with loss of both alleles

1280
01:14:42.286 --> 01:14:45.986
of a mismatch repair deficient protein, you don't see high TMB in the normal

1281
01:14:46.046 --> 01:14:46.386
tissue.

1282
01:14:47.266 --> 01:14:51.046
So even though they have replicating normal tissue, you don't

1283
01:14:51.146 --> 01:14:54.806
see a high TMB. It's only in the cancer tissue of those patients where you see

1284
01:14:54.846 --> 01:14:56.356
higher TMB. So this

1285
01:14:57.406 --> 01:15:01.166
and other approaches like the Niafor approach may not induce a higher mutational

1286
01:15:01.186 --> 01:15:03.306
burden or injury to normal tissues.

1287
01:15:04.356 --> 01:15:07.986
The clinical trial with temozolomide, cisplatin, and PD-1 blockade in

1288
01:15:08.086 --> 01:15:11.546
chemo-refractory and mismatch repair deficiency improved overall survival

1289
01:15:11.906 --> 01:15:15.406
when patients acquired an MMRD genotype, high TMB,

1290
01:15:15.966 --> 01:15:19.246
and mismatch repair deficiency. If you didn't, those patients had a shorter

1291
01:15:19.326 --> 01:15:22.386
survival. And we think that this warrants further investigation.

1292
01:15:23.146 --> 01:15:26.686
One other thing I'll point out here is it does talk about the

1293
01:15:26.706 --> 01:15:30.306
importance of clonality. We're inducing a massively

1294
01:15:30.366 --> 01:15:31.206
subclonal tumor,

1295
01:15:32.006 --> 01:15:35.766
and even if we just look at experimentally in the mice and the

1296
01:15:35.786 --> 01:15:38.186
preclinical models, they're still highly immunogenic.

1297
01:15:38.726 --> 01:15:42.686
And so I think that the theory around clonality may be

1298
01:15:42.726 --> 01:15:46.246
applicable to one tumor type, but it may not be applicable to

1299
01:15:46.306 --> 01:15:49.205
other tumor types like mismatch repair deficiency.

